Behans - what they called Behans club and our - I'm still in it yet and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15294545 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270951 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 
It was Behans it was on the Crescent - Behans Friendly Society, something else now but - when me mum died and that I said to Alf Hill, you might as well take 
these, I didn't want them because when me mother died there was two - a couple of them at home not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7809043 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 
 and I'd put them in penny clubs for fear anything happened to 'em you see. Penny - yes, burial clubs like and - to tell you the truth it's only coupl
e of years I've drawn them all out because I'd lost me clubman and he kept coming about eight - it was eight and nine and odd, well it's a lot for penny clubs. He only come about every year or every twice a year this fellow so I thought, right. I said, oh
 I'm getting shot of these. I asked them all did they want them. I said, I've paid 'em all them years, these pennies and - I might as well.
