\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270951 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 Oh well, that w
as - me mum when - when me father died with what club money we had - twenty-five pound I can remember what I drawn on him and - we - our - so when it - it was coming we was going to the Isle of Man, so I said, right mum, come on we're taking you with you 
f
or holiday. She looked so thin and that. And I spent - I blewed the lot in for - on holiday in the Isle of Man for the lot of us for my husband and the kids and - me mother, we took me mother with - and I think it was our Rosie that she had young at home,
 
took her. And - then our Mag took her - later on to Blackpool for a week on hers. It's blood money, let - get rid of it. Yes. Well we - we used to say - they used to say like that, there's always been a feeling about club money, you know, well they used t
o be I don't think it's as bad now though. Money's money now isn't it? But they used to think it was kind of thing tainted.
\par 
