\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270951 MB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 She did fret over him, and I kept - while we was away at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14765897\charrsid7603217 Isle}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217 
 of Man, especially when we'd had her out for a drink and she'd start crying I'd say, what's to do with you? She say, well when you've loved and lost after all them years, forty odd years with one man. I thought, go on, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14765897\charrsid7603217 ger off}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217  - you know, to myself, the way - 'cos she'd had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14765897\charrsid7603217 terrible}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14364513\charrsid7603217  unhappy life with her - with him. I told you she had - she had a baby after I did and - our Walter was ten month old and she had this baby and it was dead born. And - her last baby 
and it was dead born and it was born with a black eye and 'cos I can see it now in that bedroom up on the - bit of an old dresser we had upstairs and the midwife, a Mrs Booth she was out of Broughton, she'd fetched me into the world so me mother'd had her
 
over them all and she said, now listen Katie, she said, you can't put up with this, she said, there's a law now out to stop anything like this. Has he been knocking you about? And there she said she'd fell and caught herself - fell and caught her eye on t
he corner of the dresser or something like that. She wouldn't even then. She wouldn't turn on him then, see. But - well he would have been about - four - it was a little boy, he'd have been about forty-six I should think. Oh, still born, yes.
